## 13. Link Management

### Internal Links Must Always Work

Every link in the application must resolve correctly in ALL environments.

| Environment | Internal Links | Cross-Site Links |
|-------------|----------------|------------------|
| Local dev | `localhost:3000/page` | Other localhost ports or use env vars |
| Vercel Preview | Preview URL `/page` | Other preview URLs via env vars |
| Production | Production URL `/page` | Production URLs via `SITE_CONFIG` |

### Link Implementation Rules

```tsx
// CORRECT: Use relative paths for same-site internal links
<Link href="/about">About</Link>
<Link href="/services/therapy">Therapy</Link>

// CORRECT: Use SITE_CONFIG for cross-site links in monorepo
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '@/lib/site-config'  // or your config location
<a href={`${SITE_CONFIG.otherSite.url}/services`}>Other Site Services</a>

// WRONG: Hardcoded URLs
<a href="https://yourdomain.com/about">About</a>  // NO!
<a href="http://localhost:3000/about">About</a>       // NO!
```

### Cross-Site Link Matrix (Monorepo Pattern)

For multi-site builds, use a centralized config:

| From Site | To Site | Use |
|-----------|---------|-----|
| Site A | Site B | `SITE_CONFIG.siteB.url` |
| Site B | Site A | `SITE_CONFIG.siteA.url` |
| Any | Main | `SITE_CONFIG.main.url` |

Define your site URLs in a shared config file that reads from environment variables.

### Link Validation Checklist (Every Build)

- [ ] All navigation links work
